+## Risk / Conflict Controls
+
+- Historical evidence in the TODOs includes superseded behavior such as `Datas`, occurrence-level location overrides, top-level Admin `Filtros`, sticky Home filters, Discovery primitive line, and Map subfilters. None of that evidence can close current Store Release rows.
+- The orchestrator must not implement worker slices. If a validation failure appears, it is routed back to the owning worker unless the edit is strictly merge-conflict resolution or minimal reconciliation glue.
+- Final browser/device journeys are derived from the TODO matrices, not ad hoc memory.
+- Web validation must run against a runtime serving the current reconciliation build. A reachable stale bundle triggers rebuild/reprobe before blocker classification.
+- CRUD and mutation rows must mutate local/non-main runtime data through real admin/backend paths; mock-only or source-only evidence is insufficient.
