+## Dependency Graph
+- `SR-A` hard-blocks `SR-B` because typed filters depend on canonical entity/type/taxonomy projections and label snapshots.
+- `SR-C` is independent and can run in parallel with `SR-A`.
+- `SR-D` is mostly independent, but any event occurrence snapshot/projection work must sequence after `SR-A` or be reconciled against the `SR-A` branch before integration.
+- `SR-B` package core can begin after `SR-A` is locally green; its Event/EventOccurrence source adapter should wait until `SR-D` stabilizes the occurrence detail/read model.
+- Final Store Release validation must run only after `SR-A`, `SR-C`, `SR-D`, and `SR-B` are integrated into the orchestrator reconciliation branch.
