+## Execution Waves
+Waves are internal orchestration controls, not feedback checkpoints. After this plan is approved, the orchestrator advances autonomously between waves and stops only for a mandatory user decision, scope change, conflict with a governing TODO, real blocker, or explicit validation waiver.
+
+### Wave 0 - Preflight / Approval
+- Confirm this plan is approved with `APROVADO`.
+- Re-read the four governing TODOs and verify no `Blocked` qualifier changed after this artifact was written.
+- Run branch/readiness preflight and confirm the base is `origin/dev`.
+- Create the orchestrator reconciliation branch and initial worker worktrees only after approval.
+
+### Wave 1 - Independent Foundations
+- Run `WS-A Taxonomy snapshots` and `WS-C Rich text fidelity` in parallel.
+- Keep ownership disjoint: `WS-A` owns taxonomy projection/snapshot contract; `WS-C` owns long text fidelity/limits/rendering.
+- **Gate to next wave:** `SR-A` is locally green and reconciled into the orchestrator branch. `SR-C` may integrate independently when green.
+
+### Wave 2 - Event Occurrences + Filter Package Core
+- Start `WS-D Multi occurrence UX` after `SR-A` projection contract is available in reconciliation.
+- Start `WS-B Typed filters package` package/core/catalog work after `SR-A` is green; hold Event/EventOccurrence source adapter until `WS-D` stabilizes occurrence read/detail semantics.
+- **Gate to next wave:** `SR-D` occurrence contract is stable enough for filter source registration, and `WS-B` package core is green in reconciliation.
+
+### Wave 3 - Public Filter Surface Integration
+- Complete `WS-B` integrations for Map, Home Events, and Discovery Account Profiles.
+- Preserve current Map visual behavior for selected primary filters; apply approved subfilter behavior and persisted selection recovery.
+- Ensure backend queries return filtered results directly. Do not hide missing backend behavior with local post-fetch filtering.
+- **Gate to next wave:** all three public surfaces use the canonical package and pass real-backend filter validation.
+
+### Wave 4 - Consolidated Store Release Validation
+- Run the union of required Laravel, Flutter, web, and mobile checks from the orchestrator reconciliation branch.
+- Validate cross-feature interactions: taxonomy labels in event/profile details and lists, multi-occurrence event details, rich text rendering, filters on Map/Home/Discovery, persisted obsolete selections, empty/loading/error states.
+- **Gate to completion:** reconciliation branch is green or every missing validation lane is recorded as an explicit blocker/waiver.
