+## Definition of Done
+
+- [x] Public Home/Event list remains occurrence-first and occurrence-card-only.
+- [x] Event detail route can represent selected occurrence context without changing event identity.
+- [x] The public `Datas` tab is removed from event detail.
+- [x] Public event detail uses `Programação` as the multi-occurrence navigation surface when the event has programação in at least one occurrence.
+- [x] Single-occurrence public event detail still exposes `Programação` when that sole occurrence has programação, but does not show a date selector when no alternate dates exist.
+- [x] The `Programação` section renders a date selector for multi-occurrence events, highlights the selected occurrence/date, and updates the selected occurrence route query when another date is chosen.
+- [x] The `Programação` date selector uses the approved visual contract: date on the first line, weekday on the second line, no `Atual`, no time text, minimum width without weekday wrapping, and horizontal scroll for many dates.
+- [x] A selected occurrence without programação renders an empty state inside `Programação` when another occurrence in the event has programação.
+- [x] If no occurrence has programação, `Programação` is absent and direct `tab=programming` entry falls back to `Sobre`.
+- [x] Tenant-admin can create/edit multiple occurrences while preserving the first-occurrence baseline.
+- [x] Tenant-admin single-occurrence editing exposes that sole occurrence's `Programação` directly in the event form; after adding a second date, the direct editor disappears from the root form and the preserved programação is managed only from the relevant occurrence editor/card.
+- [x] Occurrences no longer expose or persist location override as an approved field.
+- [x] Programação items can optionally reference a location Account Profile that owns a Map POI; free-text location input is not accepted as the source of truth.
+- [x] Programação item participant selection is occurrence-first: items reference only profiles already linked to the same occurrence, with optional inline add-to-occurrence from the item editor.
+- [x] Programação cards render time, optional explicit title, shared Account Profile chips, and optional location affordance without empty placeholder space when optional data is absent.
+- [x] If a programação item title is empty, the public card does not derive a fallback title from an Account Profile; it renders only the participant chips.
+- [x] If a programação item has only an explicit title, that title stays vertically centered relative to the time pill.
+- [x] Shared Account Profile chips used by event/programação cards keep avatar/icon visible and truncate long labels with single-line ellipsis inside chip bounds.
+- [x] Tapping a programação item location opens the corresponding Map POI.
+- [x] `Como Chegar` lists the default event location plus all programação item Account Profile/POI locations, with the default event location as the primary card and only additional distinct locations as complementary cards.
+- [x] `Como Chegar` renders the subtitle `Outros endereços relacionados` only when at least one additional distinct location exists.
+- [x] `Como Chegar` deduplicates repeated locations by canonical Account Profile/POI identity and never repeats the default location inside the complementary block.
+- [x] Tenant-admin Events list is occurrence-first: future/later occurrences remain visible even when the first occurrence has ended, each visible occurrence can open the Event edit screen, and editing preserves the event aggregate plus selected occurrence context.
+- [x] Tests include positive and negative coverage for every optional field/section plus explicit deduplication coverage.
